records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (22 pages) SENTENCING HEARING commencing 10-23-2015 received and filed.

Defendant Raynard Mukes in court with attorney Daniel Gordon Mitchell.  Defendant Raynard Mukes in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
cab
Parties are here for sentencing.  Statement by the state and defense.  Upon inquiry of the Court, State advises they have complied with victim notification. 
.
As to count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 70 months in the Wisconsin State Prisons, with credit for 132 days time served, concurrent with count 2 and 3. The court ordered  CONFINEMENT of 32 months and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 38 months with the following conditions:
     *  Successfully complete any counseling and/or
         treatment deemed appropriate.
     *  Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, including the DV and DNA surcharges and his 
        supervision fees during his period of extended supervision.
     *  No contact with firearms.
     *  The Court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence. 
         Defendant was informed that he is Ineligible Voting until his rights are reinstated. 
     *  Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs, pursuant to 973.047 of Wisconsin 
        statutes.
.
As to count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 70 months in the Wisconsin State Prisons, with credit for 132 days time served, concurrent with count 1 and 3. The court ordered  CONFINEMENT of 32 months and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 38 months with the following conditions:
     *  Successfully complete any counseling and/or
         treatment deemed appropriate.
     *  Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, including the DV and DNA surcharges and his 
        supervision fees during his period of extended supervision.
     *  No contact with firearms.
     *  The Court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence. 
         Defendant was informed that he is Ineligible Voting until his rights are reinstated. 
     *  Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs, pursuant to 973.047 of Wisconsin 
        statutes.
.
As to count 3:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 60 days at the House of Correction, concurrent with counts 1 and 2,  with credit for 132 days.
Defendant to pay all applicable costs, assessments and surcharges, including the DV and DNA surcharges from bail on deposit.  If there is no posted bail the defendant is to pay the costs and surcharges within one year of today's date, failure to pay the costs and surcharges will result in a civil judgment.
Court advises the defendant he may not possess a firearm; is to provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  
Appeal rights given.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

The defendant is advised that as a convicted felon he/she may not carry or possess any firearms.  
The defendant is advised of his/her appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and Wisconsin Abuse Program.
.
Received and filed:  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, credit form.

Defendant Raynard Mukes in court with attorney Daniel Gordon Mitchell.  Defendant Raynard Mukes in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
cab
Case was calendared for a trial today.  The defendant wants to change his plea.
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion, court ordered all 3 counts amended. The court removed all of the "habitual criminality" penalty enhancers from all of the counts, and the state agreed not to proceed with the prosecution of intimidation of a witness charges. 
As to all 3 counts as amended.
.Defendant changes his plea to NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea questionnaire received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
The court ordered the defendant remanded for sentencing.
Case adjourned for a sentencing hearing in Branch 36.
  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
